<title type="html"><![CDATA[3/14(Thu.) Pay cut, the way to survive at work for women over 40/ Do zodiac signs reveal who we really are(host:Wil)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=263&amp;p=279#p279"><![CDATA[
Topic 1: Pay cut, the way to survive at work for women over 40? ( <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://today.line.me/TW/pc/article/ZWJvgQ?utm_source=lineshare">https://today.line.me/TW/pc/article/ZWJ ... =lineshare</a><!-- m -->)<br /><br />After reading discussions: <br />1.Retell the case in English as a group. <br />2.Do you agree to the idea that Lee Yun, the lady in the case, or any other worker, should offer pay cut to hold onto her jobs? Why or why not? <br />3.What should Lee Yun do to survive if her friend didn't have any job offer? <br />4.Why would women's age be such a big deal in local corporate culture? <br />5.If you were in Lee Yun's shoes, what would you have done differently?<br />Topic 2: Do zodiac signs reveal who we really are?<br /> <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.thoughtco.com/your-zodiac-sign-lesson-plan-1212277">https://www.thoughtco.com/your-zodiac-s ... an-1212277</a><!-- m --> <br /><br />After reading discussions: <br />1.Do you think our personality is shaped by zodiac signs, or affected by our experiences? In what ways? <br />2.How has your personality changed since you were out of school? <br />3.If you could change one aspect of your personality, what would you change?<br />4.What personality traits do you think are most important for a friend to have? A spouse? A boss? A teacher? <br />5.Have you ever heard the expression “You can’t judge the book by its cover”? What does it mean?<br />6.Agenda<br />7:00-7:25 Greetings and free talk<br />7:25-7:30 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />(Session I)<br />7:30 ~ 8:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />8:10 ~ 8:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />8:25 ~ 8:30pm Regrouping<br />(Session II)<br />8:30 ~9:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />9:10 ~9:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />9:25 ~9:30pm Concluding remarks/feedback from newcomers<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第一區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=89">AndrewWang</a> — Thu Mar 07, 2019 11:10 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
